text:
5 years ago today was hands down the worst day of my life. i lost my first love,  my hero, my inspiration and the only man that has treated me like a queen unconditionally.  i can pretend and say that its okay because you're in a better place now,  which i know you are in heaven with god, but nothing was wrong with you. you should be here.  you were healthy and happy so your departure is still hard for me to understand.  all too sudden. the selfish part of me still feels that you would be happier here with your two grandsons that im raising with the values that you instilled in me. they know about you,  they love you and they need you. however, i do know that you are watching over us and you're our guardian angel.  so you're never too far.  you're probably right next to me now shaking your head about this post because i'm sure that we in the flesh still don't truly understand the beauty of the spiritual world aka the other side and that your spirit has been around us the whole time.  i don't know.  i just miss you.  i need you.  we need you. rest in peace my little baby genius.  i love you. .
.
.

in this episode i talk about the foundation of childhood being set and carried into adulthood, how self talk can continue to manifest failure, and why/how i came up with the concept of think unbroken.

this weeks challenge is to make eye contact with yourself in the mirror for 5 seconds and tell yourself that you love you! (i love me) do this every day for the next week!

if you have questions that you would like to have me answer or any thoughts that you would like to share email them to michael@michaelunbroken.com or dm me on fb, insta, or twitter!

link is in my bio.

text:
he ran to his room
and he locked the door
for he had to get away 
from the dark man that followed

he held his face
in his cold, wet hands
and he cried oh so softly
while the man came to the door "i never did anything"
all were lies
"i would never do that"
says the drug addict

he opened the door 
to find no one there
that's when he realized
it was an illusion
#poem #poetry #aesthetic #aestheticpost #dark #depression #anxiety #ptsd #metoo

text:
el paso de diego boneta por el festival de viña del mar se esta  viendo empañado por un escándalo de acoso sexual.

ocurrió cuando la actriz y conductora daniela palavecino se acercó al mexicano para entrevistarlo, le coquetea y dice que es una tradición del festival que las animadoras y el jurado deben darse un beso en la boca. diego duda y pregunta a los presentes, y le dicen que no lo haga, palavecino le pide que haga caso omiso y finalmente se besan.

en medio del debate que se desató por quienes opinan si fue acoso o no, el propio boneta respondió en twitter un link de la noticia escribiendo " #metoo "

haciendo referencia al movimiento que busca denunciar y hacer público los casos de conducta sexual inapropiada.

aunque daniela ya había tocado el tema, y hasta pedido disculpas, en vista del mensaje del protagonista de luis miguel, la serie, volvió hablar a través de instagram stories. "vi el mensaje que puso en twitter diego boneta sobre el #metoo. nunca quise que se sintiera incómodo en ningún momento, mucho menos acosado, pero yo vivó la situación de una manera muy diferente". continuó: "sentí su aprobación en todo momento, y siempre lo vi como una situación en la que dos actores querían participar de un contenido entretenido bajo el contexto de un programa de televisión". palavecino reflexiono: "como persona, como mujer y como chilena estoy totalmente en contra del acoso, y de verdad que siento mucho que todo haya llegado hasta este punto. y si diego se sintió acosado, le pido mis disculpas.

text:
an innocent wish - the first time i tried to kill myself, i was five years old. i was often beaten, punished, threatened and emotionally abused by my parents, teachers and extended family. then, i was sexually abused by my aunt and later by a cousin, who was lot older than me. i couldn't explain my fear, pain and angst to my parents as i feared punishment and more pain inflicted on my young body and soul. that's when i happened upon a movie, where a disheveled woman, hung herself and someone narrating after, that she's in a better place and that no one would hurt her anymore. the five year old me, without a concept of death or suicide, tried to kill myself. when all the other kids were playing, i sat on the swing and wrung my neck with the rope. i was so happy that i was going to die and i awaited death. but, unfortunately i failed and i lived, to be thrown in the pangs of life.

text:
it’s okay to not be okay. 
it seems that our hearts were meant to break. 
we will ache and cry and sometimes, we will want to die.
it’s okay.
we will collect ourselves up off the ground
we will avenge our losses and pull through this stronger
f.k. phillips

it is a deeper look at the #metoo movement in india, for which i’ve collaborated with the polis project ( @thepolisproject ). if you think this message is important, relevant or have faced similar questions in discussions about the movement, please consider sharing this!

text:
om 1 vecka är det internationella kvinnodagen pga:
♀️kvinnor misshandlas varje dag i sverige, oftast av en man i nära relation. ♀️kvinnor dödas varje månad i sverige, oftast av en man i nära relation till kvinnan ♀️kvinnor tjänar fortfarande mindre än män med samma jobb.
♀️7 av 10 chefer är män.
♀️kvinnor gör mer av obetalt hemarbete än män
♀️kvinnor och flickor går med nycklar i en knuten näve under mörka kvällar pga att de vet inte om mannen/pojken de möter är en snäll människa eller våldtäktsman, det går nämligen inte att se utanpå. här kommer "manshatet" in som en del påstår att alla feminister har. det kan nog uttryckas så ibland, för hur faan ska en kvinna veta. jag vågar påstå att alla kvinnor jag känner, inkl mig själv har någon gång sprungit hem från en spårvagn med nycklar i näven pga läskig man som stirrar och sen följt efter, eller liknande.

gratulera inte på kvinnodagen. uppmärksamma den för vad den är. en vilja till ett jämställt samhälle, för alla♀️ källa: seb, samt läs tidningar så står om våldtäkter, mord och kvinnomisshandel typ varje vecka...
#metoo #internationellakvinnodagen #feminism #kämpatillsammanskompis #rainbowwarrior #civilkurage #varhögljuddtaplatsvihållervarandrashändernärdetblirläskigt #jämlikhet #allabordevarafeminister #allaslikavärde #patriarkatetfallerinomdinlivstid

we are starting a compaign called "advocating self defense techniques" to create awareness among people about the self defence techniques they can use to avoid being in any uncomfortable situation.
.
we are gathering content and we want to directly communicate with people on what their take on the whole thing is.
.
we want you all to talk about your personal experiences. you can share it by simply emailing us because it's about time, we speak up, it's about time we say no. .
we'll share your stories with other people on different social platforms and please entrust us with your personal information. no, we won't share your name, age, location, all the confidential information will be safe with us.
.

.

.

to celebrate #womenshistorymonth this march, we'll be sharing some of lamport hall's most inspiring women with you each week!
.
to start us off is vere isham, born 1686, daughter of the 4th baronet. when her mother died in 1713, her father was overwhelmed with grief. vere took it upon herself to oversee the running of the estate. she never married, largely due to her tireless dedication to lamport.
.
.

text:
the chrysalis is a dank dark place; metamorphosis, a fierce force of nature to freedom; a daily tug of war. self vs. divine. the pupa's struggles are acceptance-surrender, innately crafted to know when & how to yield to the journey—reconstruction of ♥️ & soul, body & mind. she struggles to graciously receive this process—a sacred gift from divine, ordained by his first breath of life during creation. at times she's combative, reluctant;  movements seem to break her from the safe chrysalis she calls home. it seems she's battling against the divine. as she clings to the vine she's 100% dependent—boldly choosing faith, growing stronger. unable to see the end result, she continues to fight her way out—yeilding to the process. at a cellular level, her rapid transformation takes place. divine's purpose is to turn her into a creature of awestruck beauty; to add color where there was none, vibrant energy—unhindered mobility where lethargy once was limiting her.
her plan for self—to remain comfortable in the dirt & dark-the status quo, the unknown, to remain invisible. or worse, she'd rather revel in lies the ugliness proclaimed. she’d hide from her god-given beauty keeping it from others—from herself.
in the midst of our struggle, we become stronger; we have stamina—we grow; we cling to the vine, “don’t let go!” the battle grip is necessary; grit is needed for complete metamorphosis to take place, internally & externally. i struggled a long time to get out of my cocoon- to understand the necessity of struggle, sufferings, and pain. 40 years i battled self and divine. one day, i heard creator whisper softly, "no more; it’s finished. it's time to be seen; you are my beauty. i've given you wings; you're freed to fly!" more flying- evolving! more authenticity! where is god "metamorphi-sizing" you or asking you to yield, to come out anew? like a butterfly are you freed to fly? is he whispering to you? #shareyourstory #lifewaywomen #lifeway #authorsofinstagram #freedominchrist ##girlswithtatoos #metamorphosis #propelwomen #girlwashyourface #girlstopapologizing #motivation #redemption #metoo #madeformore #risingstrong
name: Debra Muniz MA, CPLC, IAC

text:
اقسام ازدواج در ایران باستان:

در مورد انواع پیوند زناشویی در ایران باستان گفتنی است که زن و مرد به ۵ صورت و تحت عناوین پادشاه زن- چاکر زن- ایوک زن- ستر زن- خودسر زن پیوند زناشویی می‌بستند که هر یک جداگانه به شرح زیر است:

۱- پادشاه زن : این نوع ازدواج به حالتی گفته می‌شد که دختری پس از رسیدن به سن بلوغ با موافقت پدر و مادر خود با پسری ازدواج می‌کرد و پادشاه زن از کاملترین حقوق و مزایای زناشویی برخوردار بود و کلا" همه دخترانی که برای نخستین بار و با رضایت پدر و مادر ازدواج می‌کردند، پیوند زناشویی آنان تحت عنوان پادشاه زن ثبت می‌شد.. ۲- چاکر زن : این نوع ازدواج به حالتی اطلاق می‌شد که زنی بیوه به عقد و ازدواج با مرد دیگری در می‌آمد. این زن با زندگی در خانه شوهر دوم خود حقوق و مزایای پادشاه زن را در سراسر زندگی مشترک دارا بود، ولی پس از مرگ آیین کفن و دفن و سایر مراسم مذهبی اش تا سی روزه توسط شوهر دوم یا بستگانش برگزار می‌شد. ولی هزینه های مراسم بعد از سی روزه به عهده بستگان شوهر اولش بود، چون معتقد بودند در دنیای دیگر این زن از آن نخستین شوهر خود خواهد بود و به همین علت پیوند دوم او تحت عنوان چاکر زن یاد می‌شد.
حال برای برخی ناآگاهان پیوند زناشویی از نوع چاکر زن را اختیار کردن زن صیغه ای توسط پدران ما در گذشته قلمداد کرده و پادشاه زن را زن عقدی بیان می‌کنند که صحت ندارد.

۳- ایوک زن: این نوع ازدواج زمانی اتفاق می‌افتاد که مردی دختر یا دخترانی داشت و فرزند پسر نداشت و ازدواج تنها دختر یا کوچکترین دخترش تحت عنوان ایوک ثبت می‌شد و رسم بر این بود که اولین پسر تولد یافته از این ازدواج به فرزندی پدر دختر در می‌آمد و به جای نام پدرش نام پدر دختر را بعد از نامش می‌آوردند و این نوع ازدواج باعث شده که برخی افراد غیر مطلع برچسب ازدواج با محارم را به زرتشتیان بزنند و اظهار کنند که پدر با دختر خود ازدواج می‌کرده است. اینک اشتباه افراد ناآگاه کاملا" مشخص شد و اتهام ازدواج با محارم کاملا" مردود است.

۴- ستر زن: وقتی که فرد بالغی بدون ازدواج در می‌گذشت، پدر و مادر یا خویشان این فرد موظف بودند به خرج خود و به یاد فرد درگذشته دختری را به ازدواج پسری در می‌آورند. شرط این نوع ازدواج آن بود که دختر و پسر متعهد می‌شدند که در آینده یکی از پسران خود را به فرزند خواندگی فرد درگذشته بدون زن و فرزند درآورند.

۵- خودسر زن: اگر دختری و پسری پس از رسیدن به سن بلوغ برخلاف میل والدین خود خواستار ازدواج با یکدیگر می‌شدند و مصر بر این امر نیز بودند

اولین پسر تولد یافته از این ازدواج به فرزندی پدر دختر در می‌آمد و به جای نام پدرش نام پدر دختر را بعد از نامش می‌آوردند و این نوع ازدواج باعث شده که برخی افراد غیر مطلع برچسب ازدواج با محارم را به زرتشتیان بزنند و اظهار کنند که پدر با دختر خود ازدواج می‌کرده است . اینک اشتباه افراد ناآگاه کاملا `` مشخص شد و اتهام ازدواج با محارم کاملا `` مردود است . ۴- ستر زن : وقتی که فرد بالغی بدون ازدواج در می‌گذشت، پدر و مادر یا خویشان این فرد موظف بودند به خرج خود و به یاد فرد درگذشته دختری را به ازدواج پسری در می‌آورند . شرط این نوع ازدواج آن بود که دختر و پسر متعهد می‌شدند که در آینده یکی از پسران خود را به فرزند خواندگی فرد درگذشته بدون زن و فرزند درآورند . ۵- خودسر زن : اگر دختری و پسری پس از رسیدن به سن بلوغ برخلاف میل والدین خود خواستار ازدواج با یکدیگر می‌شدند و مصر بر این امر نیز بودند

text:
freedom to be bold--be fresh, be re-energized, re-invigorated. be you! there's only one you! god danced with joy when you arrived.  he told his angels to sing.  embrace this! choose joy today! choose  to believe you have purpose, because you do! your dna is unlike any other; own it, flaunt it, revel in your uniqueness-- celebrate it. 
then thank god he gave you life!  every day is a "birth" day. we get the opportunity to be reborn each day-- new approach, fresh mindset, a redo! 
we can be infused with boldness and confidence by starting our day in the good book or in an attitude of humility and gratitude to god.  reap the bold, fresh, new rewards as you move closer to him. today i choose to be bold, vibrant, victorious, and fresh!

text: a portrait of courage. azata soro. burkina faso actress and victim of workplace violence. she was attacked and disfigured with a broken bottle by a director in burkina faso in 2017 while filming a tv series. for six years she was harassed by the same man who is now showcasing his series at this year’s fespaco, the panafrican film and tv festival of ouagadougou. african actresses, directors and producers came together in ouagadougou to denounce the impunity enjoyed by men in the african film industry. following #metoo in the united states and #balancetonporc in france, #memepaspeur has emerged as the hashtag with which african women in the film industry are speaking out against sexual harassment. #memepaspeur #photojournalism #documentary #africa #burkinafaso #women #portraitphotography #afp #eosr #canonfrance #canonrsa

text:
just added to our march programme as a belated #iwd2019 treat we are excited to be screening be pretty and shut up! on 11th march at 8pm

one of the most iconic actresses of the 20th century and an ardent feminist who worked almost exclusively with female directors late in her career, delphine seyrig’s work behind the camera has largely been ignored. 
in 1975 and 1976 delphine interviewed 24 female actors in france and the united states – including juliet berto, ellen burstyn, jane fonda, viva, shirley maclaine and maria schneider – about their experience across the industry. through their words, seyrig reveals the frustrations of working within the patriarchal studio system that offers a stereotypical and reductive view of women through unimaginative and regressive roles, which are still very much apparent today.

the expectation to 'be pretty and shut up' is not new, nor has it disappeared since these interviews were recorded over 40 years ago.

dir: delphine seyrig, 1976, france, 110 mins, cert: 18 tba

tickets: £5

#delphineseyrig #directedbywomen #metoo #timesup

text:
ces hommes qui m’expliquent la vie ✨
~
« toutes les femmes savent de quoi je parle »
~
 rebecca solnit évoque l’anecdote où déjà auteure de 7 livres, un homme important après lui avoir demandé sur quoi elle écrit lui demande, condescendant,  si elle a lu ce livre très important paru la même année que le sien sur le même sujet (livre qu’elle a elle-même écrit !!) 😂
il se met alors à lui expliquer doctement en quoi ce livre est brillant, sous-entendant implicitement la supériorité de cet ouvrage sur tout ce qu’elle pourrait prétendre produire, alors que lui-même... ne l’a même pas lu.
~
malheureusement la misogynie ne s’arrête pas là et tue plus de femmes tous les 3 ans qu’un 11 septembre sans que ça entraîne la même sidération ou indignation, que c’est même la première cause de mortalité chez les femmes devant tout le reste. et tout ceci dans nos sociétés occidentales, hein... pas à l’autre bout du monde !
et bizarrement, pour une fois, ce massacre ne donne pas envie aux hommes de faire une petite guerre pour régler le problème ...🤔💥
~
lecture en cours !  on en reparle bien sûr ! 😁 ~~~~~~~<<<<~~~~~>>>~~~

.
.
#repost @indonesiafeminis (@get_repost)
・・・
#repost @jaringanmuda
• • • • •
apapun gaya dan ekspresimu, kamu berhak aman dan bebas dari kekerasan seksual..!! —————— lemahnya perlindungan hukum atas kekerasan seksual tentu menjadi penghambat dalam pelaporan dan penanganan korban. belum lagi cara pandangan yang masih sering menyalahkan korban justru membuat pembatasan ruang gerak tidak ditujukan pada pelaku melainkan pada korban seperti contoh: adanya jam malam untuk perempuan, aturan berpakaian, cara berperilaku, bertutur serta kenyamanan berekspresi lainnya. hingga saat ini belum ada peringatan dan tindakan tegas bagi pelaku, sehingga berdampak pada pembiaraan kasus kekerasan seksual yang membuat korban semakin diam dan malu untuk melaporkan.

pelaku kekerasan seksual bisa siapa saja. bisa dari orang yang sama sekali tidak kita kenal atau bahkan orang yang justru dekat dengan kita, seperti teman sebaya, teman satu komunitas, pacar, pengajar dan sebagainya. kita tahu bahwa yang menjadi korban kekerasan seksual tidak selalu perempuan, korbannya juga bisa laki-laki. oleh karenanya laki-laki harus turut mengambil peran dari perlawanan terhadap perjuangan untuk menghapuskan kekerasan seksual.

apa sih manfaatnya dengan kita turut ambil peran dalam
penghapusan kekerasan seksual?

kita dapat memastikan terciptanya ruang aman, nyaman, bebas berekspresi dan bebas dari kekerasan seksual, agar orang-orang terdekat dan teman-teman kita tidak menjadi korban selanjutnya. 
karena kasus-kasus pelecehan dan kekerasan seksual dapat terjadi pada siapa saja dan di mana saja, oleh karena itu perlawanan terhadapnya pun harus hadir dari siapa saja dan di mana saja semakin banyak teman-teman yang turut bersuara, maka semakin besar pula perlawanan terhadap kekerasan seksual tersebut.

text: entertainment is essential in our everyday lives, it is not limited to music or movies, it is also about sports, arts, and many other recreational or leisure activities. in this era where there are numerous social movements that seek to address various issues in society like homophobia, sexual harassment, abuse, and many others. we see that with the rise of #metoo and #timesup movements, entertainers are being held accountable for their actions.  should we boycott art that has been created by people who have said or done something bad?  since 2018, the students of webster university ghana campus have been organizing an annual spring student conference, that features and discussions various topics that affect the contemporary 21st century. last year, the theme of our conference was “the double-edged sword of science and technology in social media in the 21st century”. for this year’s conference, we will be addressing the ethical issue of “the art vs. the artist”

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
this lively film tracks ginsburg’s brilliant legal career, fighting for women’s workplace rights while shrewdly also taking on cases where men suffered discrimination. it pays a moving tribute to the important role played in ginsburg’s life by her devoted husband marty, to whom she was married for over 50 years until his death. 
it also highlights her most compelling pronouncements, such as that in shelby county v holder in 2013, in which she argued that the regional protections of the voting rights act in preventing race discrimination were still necessary even when they appeared to have been rendered obsolete by precisely those improved conditions they continue to maintain. 
abolition was like “throwing away your umbrella in a rainstorm because you are not getting wet”.
but for good or ill, the film does not directly engage with ginsburg’s views on contemporary feminism and sexual harassment and what is sometimes derisively called identity politics. it was made well before the appointment of the self-pitying and shrill brett kavanaugh to the bench – in comparison with whom ginsburg looks even more like an intellectual giant – and so she could hardly be expected to comment on the christine blasey ford case. but she serves alongside clarence thomas, whose denial of harassment allegations from anita hill at his own confirmation hearing in 1991 is a matter of public record.
did the film-makers consider it improper to ask ginsburg anything at all about that? there is a strange silence – it would have been interesting, and highly relevant, to hear from ginsburg in general terms about the legal implications of #metoo.

text:
for our last #blackhistorymonth feature, we honor the women who started a cultural revolution, #taranaburke ✋🏿✋🏽✋🏻
-
as a child, tarana burke face multiple sexual assaults. to cope with this trauma, her mother suggested that she turn to helping her community. it was those experiences that drove burke to a life of fighting for women and girls. her work with the program just be inc., a nonprofit she founded in 2003 that focused on the overall well-being of young women of color, is what led her to first coin the phrase “me too” in 2006. but it wasn’t until 2017 that her phrase became an international phenomenon. after a tweet by actress alyssa milano, “me too” became a rallying cry for women everywhere to come forward lead a worldwide campaign to raise awareness about sexual harassment, abuse and assault in society. later that year, burke and other influential female activists were named "the silence breakers" by time magazine for their work breaking down toxic power structures and supporting survivors. burke currently serves at the girls for gender equity in brooklyn, ny as its senior director. •
•
•
•
•
•
#blackmagic #blackboymagic #blackhistory #blacklivesmatter #blackhistory2019 #bhm #metoo #sexualharrassment #westandwithsurvivors

text:
i’m going to get naked...
.
.
and share a little about who i am @lifes.dirty.secrets and why she manifested through me.
. 💥potential trigger warning💥
.
when i was a teen, instead of experiencing sex for the first time with a boy i was dating, or the boy i was head over heels for, or the “love of my young life”, i was coerced into a situation i didn’t know how to get myself out off. he was older, and i was still under age.
i said no. several times. afterwards, he dropped me at home like it was an every day event. 
by monday, everyone knew, but i told no one. he told. and i was judged for it. blamed for it. my “friends” told me “i’m disappointed in you”... “i thought you were better than that”... and said things like “i expected more from you”.
i felt hollow. broken. dirty. 
and so, so alone. i blamed myself. i told no one the real story thinking “who would believe me?”... after all, no one stopped to ask what a man in his 20’s was doing with a 17 yr old... it took the #metoo movement for me to finally share with 1 person. sharing with 1 became 2. then 3. i shared with my current friends. my true friends. sisters who have my back and hold me up when i can’t stand on my own feet alone. . 
but this is only 1 of my stories of sexual assault. abuse. disrespect. stories i was ashamed to share. my “dirty secrets”... but they shouldn’t be secrets. .
i’m still healing. i’m still letting go. i’m still learning it’s ok to tell this story. .
and so are many, many more women. #lifesdirtysecrets is a chance to share. to open the conversations. and i’m using co-author books to do so.
🔥under the covers🔥
💖soul sister series💖
come share your stories. show women we can rise. we can heal. we are enough. together, we need to raise our voices. together, we won’t just survive, we will thrive.
.
.
#metoomovement #shareyourstory #goddess #rise #dontholdback #authenticity #writeyourstory #womenempowerment #womeninspiringwomen #womensrights #mystory #nomeansno #sisterhood

text: its officially women’s history month, something i did not know existed until 2006, i was 21.... since 2017 i have featured a woman everyday of march to honor the diverse incredible intersections of womanhood!!!! to kick it off @amandangocnguyen amanda n. nguyen is the founder and ceo of rise, a non-governmental civil rights organization. she was the power behind the sexual assault survivors' rights act, one of 23 bills to pass unanimously through us congress. you may recognize her from speaking on the #metoomovement with terry crews. amanda has tirelessly worked for survivors of color and at age 28 has been nominated for a nobel peace prize. i had the honor of meeting her at the @aapiwomenlead conference in october and she is hellllaaaa cool and such a girls girl!!!! salute queen!!!!!!!!!! #amandanguyen #metoo #survivorsbillofrights #feministofcolor #nobelpeaceprizenominee #vietnameseamerican #womenshistorymonth #contentmatters #communityfirst #hellafamous

text:
• aly raisman: pushing society to change the way we view women •

in these pictures, aly is fighting the stigma around sexual assault and expressing that we, as a society have to change the way we view women. through her photo shoot with espn (top picture) and her confidently wearing a survivor swimsuit as a part of the aerie real campaign (bottom left), aly radiates fierceness and is an inspiration for others. ••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
in her interview with espn she states, “i know i am one of the few that are being heard, so i just want to do right by people.” this mindset highlights aly’s drive and dedication in changing the way our society handles sexual assault as she feels that this is “bigger than nassar.” she ultimately wants the forces that systematically devalue female bodies to be recognized and changed. 
#alyraisman #metoo #women #survivor #respect #fierce #timesup #espn

text:
this is a piece about my personal experience with sexual assault last year. i managed to get out before the situation got worse. but, i'm often haunted by nightmares from the event. sometimes, the dreams get so violent i can't sleep for the rest of the night. i haven't had any nightmares since last saturday (when i wrote this) 
if anyone out there has been a victim of sexual abuse, rape, assault or any kind of unwanted behavior/attention. there is help, there is support and justice out there.

remember that you are not worthless and you are a survivor who is resilient and  beautiful in every way. you are not alone and have my full support. ✌️❤️ - ani

text:
this afternoon an unexpected event landed me at ucla medical center to console a family that i’ve grown to love in a short period of time. just before leaving, i spoke with a woman about the event and was very surprised by what she revealed. she talked about her traumatic childhood experiences and how they directed her toward a negative path. i was humbled by the honesty and sisterhood created as we talked about trauma healing. she articulated her perspective about survivor-hood, which is strikingly similar to mine (and even talked about writing a book to be a voice for other women). to hear another woman talk about suppressing feelings & memories, growing into an understanding that she was okay as a survivor, and the pinball-like task of managing triggers echoed much of the work i’ve experienced recently. it felt like a conversation with my highest self. this was exactly what i needed after a long week and especially difficult afternoon. i have even more motivation to continue writing the blog entries that i’ve been sitting on recently. and with that, off i go...
#lifeturns #resilience #faceforward #survivor #metoo #feelings #flashbacks #triggers #mentalwellness #perspective #gratitude #writeon #runwritelive #writersofinstagram #jemilada

text: holy shit what a tiresome week it's been to be a woman, or anyone who feels vulnerable to those in power. feel like shooting lazers at abusive men fembot style!? me too! someone told me they'd been listening to diva with the fever of change on repeat this week cause they were so mad hearing about all the abusive men out there ryan adams, wil wagner, r kelly et al plus the obvious grand daddy of abusers mr pell. despite all this grotesqueness, hearing this makes me so happy because the only solace i feel that we can take from being bombarded with these stories of men abusing their power is that of support and solidarity. knowing that i've put something out into the world that is making someone feel strong is honestly the best feeling. even though this week has felt particularly tough, the fact that people are starting to take this shit, that we've been putting up with for so long, seriously, is cause to put your fist in the air and call it a win ✊🏾here is a still from our diva clip, have a watch and a rage at the patriarchy with me (link is in bio). together in rage we stand (and shoot lazers from our tits, amen). 📷 @alexcardy dop feat mega queen @radisonstyler #divawiththefeverofchange #solidarity #timesup #metoo #believewomen #feminism #women #smashthepatriachy patriarchy #yesallwomen #believesurvivors #womensreality #nomoore #iamanastywoman #everydaysexism

text:
as i was typing a blog post about the racist hate comments my reporting on the worthington-west franklin vfd ...someone posted a threat to have me raped.

he wrote "pghlesbian. wtf is that? i hope they come to my town. i'd pay a meth addict to rape them." could there be a more apt reflection of the transition from black history month (feb) to women's history month (march) in trump's america than threating to hire someone to rape me because i called out the #racism in a rural #westernpennsylvania community?

imagine how women who live in this town must feel? imagine how black and brown women feel? 
no need to post sad/angry faces or commiserate. better that you reach out to folks in #armstrongcounty and find out how you can support them. that's going to require more effort ... are we up to keep resisting? how are you investing in #resistance?

read details at pghlesbian.com 
#rapeculture #allyship #racialjustice #firedepartment #smalltown #metoo #survivor #intersectionality #technicallyacrime

text:
rp  @vswolf  @krissy_obie #mothersagainstdairy -  #milkhurts. these are not "veal" calves, who are typically male, but are rather female calves. on dairy farms, calves are stolen from their mothers shortly after birth and, more often than not, female calves are confined in isolated pens like this one for their first 2 to 3 months of life. dairy farmers love to call this lonely, deprived, motherless existence "individualized calf care." in reality, confining calves separately is considered to prevent mass spread of illness between calves, which matters only for reasons of profit. in reality, if dairy farmers really cared about the best interests of the calves, they would never be stolen from their mothers to begin with. more importantly, if dairy farmers *really* cared about the best interests of animals, they wouldn't be breeding them into a life of exploitation in the first place. dairy = motherhood invaded, exploited, commodified and destroyed. please don't support it. choose delicious plant-based alternatives instead.

footage by #arminvestigations  from their new dairy farm investigation. full investigation at secretsofdairy.com.

#repost @world
・・・
pope francis’ former top financial advisor and the vatican’s economy minister, cardinal george pell, has been found guilty of molesting choir boys more than 20 years ago, making him the highest-ranking roman catholic leader ever found guilty of sexual abuse. the 77-year-old, formally considered the third most powerful man in the vatican, was found guilty of forcing oral sex onto a 13-year-old boy after sunday mass in st. patrick’s cathedral in melbourne in 1996 when he was the city’s archbishop. he was also convicted of an assault in which he grabbed a boy’s genitals. the court heard testimony from one of the victims. the other victim died of a drug overdose in 2014, according to the bbc. sentencing proceedings are beginning on wednesday and are expected to last a few days. pell was found guilty in december, but a judge barred news outlets from publishing anything about the verdict out of concerns it would influence a jury in a second trial for an additional round of assault allegations. the suppression order was only lifted on tuesday after the second trial was canceled. pope francis expelled pell from his group of advisors in december. (📷: getty)
-

text:
dear steph
thank you. as a male teenager growing up in 2019, people expect you to toughen up alot of the time, and it is almost expected that you aren't as emotional as the female gender. but ever since i saw your directing episode today, i have been crying ever since.
you did such a phenomenal job on the #metoo storyline and you nailed it. sexual assault is something i was scared to come out and talk about for 7 years, half my life. with all of the awareness around this issue, you are making people's lives change, just because you included one important subject that needed to be heard.
you, and a few other people have saved my life. without the strength that was provided through the many positive messages i got through social media posts, clips and stories, i wouldn't be here. you saved my life. i'd really like you to notice just how much you have an impact on lives. 
thank you for including us, survivors. you are backing us up. you're the light we need in our lives. •
can you please tag stephanie? this is something i'd really like her to see ❤
@stephaniebeatriz

text:
the first time we walked in the front door of our home we saw about 5 different clashing colors just from this vantage point. they consisted of khaki, cranberry, mint green, a doo doo brown (sorry no better name for it 🤷🏼‍♀️), and bright blue. it was a time i was very thankful i could see past the chaos. i am all for each room having it’s own personality, but i’m also for the space as a whole working together.
.
the color palette we went with consisted of the calm and cool @sherwinwilliams colors - agreeable grey (sw 7029), olympus white (sw 6253), lazy gray (sw 6254), refuge (sw 6228), and sea salt (sw 6204).
.
y’all, paint is an effective way to instantly change the look of your home. taking it from warm to cool, cool to warm, wild to calm, anything you can think of the psychology of color plays a role in it. it’s one of the reasons i choose neutral tones for the walls and accessorize with pops of color. the accessories are so much easier to change out!
.
.
.
.
.

text:
time to xspose your vision! 
join us for an evening of goal setting, vision exposing and networking.

we'll provide snacks and journals. all you have to do is show up ready to learn, share, and be xsposed as the gift that you are! 
event agenda: 
create goals relevant to your vision and life, and feel supported in asking for suggestions and feedback. come to ask questions and share your story. together we will celebrate our highs and lows, related to business or otherwise, and walk away feeling inspired and connected.
itinerary:

about shirkydra roberts :
shirkydra is the ceo of i.a.m.e. (impact, aspire, motivate enterprises). she is a motivational speaker, life transformation coach, and published author. she has published two books: ‘what’s a word worth” and “just unwrap it”. as a #metoo survivor, she uses her story to motivate and inspires women to put action behind their vision. she teaches how to overcome past trauma in order to build self-love, confidence, and hope to experience emotional freedom. she has dedicated her time to leading women and the youth on overcoming daily challenges in order to reach their goals and dreams. currently, she is also serving as an engineering officer in the united states navy. 
about erynne byrd
erynne is the ceo of she’s her own consulting business that is dedicated to helping women and young girls live a more intentional life by providing the direct tools needed for them to succeed. she is a poet, published author, and inspiration speaker. she recently published her first book “a compilation of female truth”. she has spoken at numerous events to include seattle’s 2019 washington state regional girl up summit. she has hosted events such as the breaks-n-eggs brunch and had the special honor of being featured in the navy’s featured magazine. she is dedicated to bridging the gap between what people assume about being a woman of service and the actual reality. she speaks to young women on about the benefits of being discipline as well as the rewards that come with joining the ranks can be to your future. currently, she is serving as a mechanical engineer in the united states navy.
name: Shirkydra Roberts

text:
oh gosh here we go... i’m going to get deep with you guys (again). it’s not very often you will find me posting a photo of my bare face but lately i’ve been wearing a lot less make-up and learning to just love this side of me.

make-up has always been a way for me to express how i am feeling, but when i was 300lb i used it as way to help me feel better about myself.

i never wanted anyone to see the real me. i hid under clothes. i hid under makeup. i hid under my weight. i couldn’t let anyone see the real me. ever.

i was always trying to be someone else that i didn’t even know who i truly was anymore.

the process of this journey has been a shedding of my “layers” both mentally and physically, i’ve been stripping myself down to get to the very core of who i am.

my weightloss was a by product of getting my mental health in order. dealing with my depression, my binge eating and anxiety. challenging my limiting beliefs about myself and proving those nasty voices in my head wrong.

not hiding away meant being vulnerable to hurt and pain. that some scary shit. opening yourself up to the world but that power to be open and bare, that’s beautiful. 
@brenebrown said, “what makes you vulnerable, makes you beautiful”. the more layers that come off, the brighter i shine because for once i feel free to be my true self.

i’ve been through a lot of shit in my life and it feels pretty awesome to be in a place where i am living fully and not hiding myself away from the world. i am living in my vulnerability and it does feel beautiful.

what i found underneath was a powerful, creative, kind hearted, goofy yet fierce, bold wild woman.

i guess to sum it all up. if you are willing to strip away your layers, i think you will be quite surprised about what you will find underneath. ❤️ #weightlossjourney#mentalhealth#anxiety#depression#ptsd#metoo#sheisstrong#strongisbeautiful#beavisionary#selfloveclub#confidenceiskey#thursdaymotivation#selfdevelopment#weightlosstransformation#extremeweightloss#bingeeatingrecovery#bingeeatingdisorderrecovery#edwarrior#edrecovery#massiveweightloss#weightlosstips#bareface#nomakeup#thepowerofvulnerability#attitudeofgratitude

text:
raising up others is the best part of my job.⠀
.⠀
two of my career experiences with a giant non-profit that relied heavily on volunteers & counseling high school students in a low-income school district both laid a foundation for learning the importance of pouring encouragement into a person in order to see them rise up.⠀
.⠀
those both prepared me for the two jobs i have now: a stay-at-home mama and an online fitness mentor. i for sure screw up big time as a parent however when i throw encouragement at my little girls...they thrive. they become more confident to try new things. they become motivated.⠀
.⠀
for the hundreds of women i have the privilege to mentor in their fitness journey and my team of boss babes it lights my soul on fire to know that if i can play a role in showing them their worth, value and help them develop their confidence muscles that it will radically ripple throughout every aspect of their lives.⠀
.⠀
it doesn’t take some guru to lead someone else into a healthy and prosperous life.⠀
.⠀
it takes a brave one.

text:
let's #bereal for a min...in the world of #bodybuilding and #gymrats and #lifeingeneral, there is this thing called #bodyshaming. we are much too critical of our bodies. 🙋 #metoo as a #figurecompetitor it is all too easy to criticize certain parts of my body. ones that don't conform. where i hold just a bit of extra "fluff". for me, this is my upper arms and legs. i've always been self-conscious about them. even though i really don't have a reason for it, other than that dumb old comparison game. so this pic is me, half-posing my arm for you....because at the gym today, a girl that i see often but haven't talked to told me, ”#lifegoals, to get my arms to look like yours." 😍 totally made my day! maybe my week. you never know when that body part you are criticizing is someone else's goal!! so let's #celebrate those parts of us that might not be the ”standard" size or shape or whatever. and #bekind and #givecompliments, yes, even to yourself!

text:
em todos os momentos da nossa vida os detalhes fazem a diferença. e na moda não é diferente. .
um detalhe errado num look legal não vai passar desapercebido aos olhares mais atentos.
.
você pode escolher um tom de roupa neutro, não necessariamente branco ou preto, pode ser: tons em verde militar, azul marinho, marrom, tons de nude, bordô, marsala ou fendi, são escolhas que fogem do tradicional e combinam com diversas cores vivas, esse já é um detalhe que faz uma diferença enorme.
.
outro detalhe são os acessórios transformadores. você não precisa exagerar no look, basta incluir um acessório diferente e cheio de personalidade que já muda completamente a aparência.
.
se você ainda tem medo de experimentar e “ousar” nas suas escolhas, vá inserindo aos poucos, não se limite a coisas óbvias. .
seja diferente e arrisque. coloque sua personalidade para brilhar.
se vestir bem é treino diário, requer autoconhecimento e dedicação. 😉

text:
a letter to the girl who forgets to love herself...
________
because let’s be honest here, i know i’m guilty of neglecting myself and i am pretty sure i’m not alone. but here’s the thing, everyone of us is capable of fostering self-love and every single one of us should make that a goal. why?
________
simply put self-love means to fully accept and allow your true, natural self. it lays the foundation down for you to have a happier, healthier relationship with yourself and with others. sure, it takes some work but it’s soooo worth it!
___________
luckily, our friends at @wellbeingtrust have given us some great ways to boost self-love so be sure to swipe ⬅️ to read the list! i’d also strongly suggest saving the list because it’s worth rereading over and over again! and as always, feel free to tag or share this! ❤️ #beheard #bethere #bewell #herfeed

text:
paring down your life to just two suitcases and a carry-on is a powerful way to realize which possessions are most important to you. for me, this is one of the precious pieces that moved over the sea and now hangs in my living room.
.
.
"wasp nest" was a series i created a few years ago that explored home, intimate relationships and became a therapeutic way to find healing from the bites of stinging creatures.
.
.
here i used clay to sculpt mud dauber nests that encrust the model much like a wing. you can find a collection of the original #gumbichromate pieces posted on my website, amyparrish.com (link in bio). most of the series still resides in usa and is being managed by an art rep who i can put you in touch with.
.
.
.
.
.

text: il est temps que je parle . je n ai pas pu le faire avant les mots étaient trop douloureux. il y a eu #metoo et #balancetonporc . depuis hier avec #memepaspeur j’ai raconté que moi aussi j ai été victime de harcèlement sexuel et d agression sexuelle sur deux tournages en afrique. c’était il y a très longtemps. la douleur a été engloutie. aujourd’hui je suis prête à parler pour aider à libérer cette parole et récupérer ma vie. je suis une resiliente. je vais mettre en place une plateforme d ‘écoute pour que les jeunes femmes et jeunes hommes qui subissent ça ne se sentent plus jamais seuls . la reconstruction ne peut se faire qu’en libérant cette parole. je vais travailler pour mettre en place une charte pour les tournages en afrique. la peur doit changer de camps . je n ai plus peur. je veux que mes drames servent à aider ceux qui ont encore les mots coincés dans leur douleur. je rappelle que ce sont des crimes passibles de prison. ne faisons plus comme si ils n existaient pas! merci au collectif des cinéastes non alignées pour cette table ronde sur la place des femmes dans le cinéma africain. merci à mon mari @geoffroytekeyan mes amies et sœurs #hortenseassaga @aissamaiga @huguettemalamba pour leur soutien et amour indéfectibles. il y a eu #metoo aux usa #balancetonporc en france il y a désormais #memepaspeur en afrique. #actress #metoo #balancetonporc #memepaspeur #harcelementsexuel #agressionsexuelle #resilience #freespeech #ivorycoast #senegal #cotesdarmor #womanempowerment #warrior #cineastesnonalignees #fespaco2019 #nadegebeaussondiagne photo #hortenseassaga #nofilter #picoftheday #blackbeauty #blackgirlmagic #sorority

text:
#womanism is a term first coined by author & activist alice walker as another name for #blackfeminism .

it is an inclusive social movement similar to feminism, but with a central focus on women of color. walker felt the need to step away from the word feminist that for so long had been associated with only helping white women advance in society. 
being informed on why people identify a certain way (i.e. womanist vs feminist) allows us to think about how we identify ourselves. 
how do you identify as a feminist?

text:
#whiteribboncampaign #metoo #survivor #sexualassault #awareness #upstanders ...
a sexual assault can happen anywhere, anytime and to anyone.

i have many truths to share but i'm sharing this one with all of you as we embark on the 25th white ribbon campaign in our syracuse community with @verahouseinc leading the way.

you can make a difference by being an upstander in our community rather than being silent as a bystander.

three months ago, i was forcibly touched in public while reporting in the field. dozens of bystanders, many of whom made eye contact with me during and after the assault, stood silently.

the incident happened in mere moments while i was recording an on-camera piece and doing my own video work during that day. the trauma of it shook me to the core -- opening my eyes to the horrific truth that sexual assault can happen anywhere -- even in plain sight with others standing by. being violated while others witnessed it and stayed silent felt like a secondary assault.

thanks to the support of my husband, my family and friends, co-workers and the onondaga county sheriff's office, i have worked toward healing and regaining a sense of comfort while i'm out reporting in the field.

as a survivor of past incidents, i know healing and trust are possible. i also know that when we support one another and speak up for what's right, we can make change happen.

together, we can be upstanders. we can all pledge to not condone, be silent or be complicit when it comes to sexual assault and domestic violence.
name: Farah Jadran

text:
day 28 : ends.
my best friend and colleague from my time in dc (2016-18), michael beaver, left this life prematurely, at age 39, last summer. i write about him today for many reasons. this photo of us, snapped by @melcheeksdvm when michael and i administered the 2016 presidential election electoral ballot counting, captures us perfectly. we had each other’s backs, through thick and thin.
.
michael was the smartest, most creative, and most dynamic lawyer i have ever known. our shared, dry sense of humor brought comic relief to our jobs as senate parliamentarians. we were both dc-outsiders. we’d laugh until we cried at subreddit and youtube videos. we’d one-up each other with buys from the walgreens as seen on tv aisle: he won with a bob ross chia pet. we were both cat people and survived on plant-based diets (his was mainly candy and cereal).
.
during the most difficult professional experience of my life, michael took the time to not only teach and advocate for me, but to care. an artist himself, he was genuinely interested in my knitting projects. he’d ask about the patterns, fiber, and color ways. he’d ask (and make jokes) about my dating life as he’d accompany me from the capitol to union station on nights i didn’t take a car service home.
.
michael was a lifeline. but two months after i settled my senate employment discrimination claim, left dc, and started my life over in madison, we lost michael.
.
i can honestly say that i don’t know whether i’d be here today without michael’s role in my life. he constantly reassured me that i was a good friend, lawyer, and colleague. and that i was wonderful as i was. his friendship is woven into my being and gives me energy to actively share positivity, creativity, and loving kindness.
.
while michael has left this physical world, his legacy has all but ended.
.
#ends #beginnings #day28 #yarnlovechallenge #yarnlovechallenge2019 #senate #lawyer #cspan #caa #metoo #talkaboutit #ibelieveyou #foreverfriends #bluesteel #support #parliamentarians #dc #payitforward #artists #creativity #knit #draw #artitation #knititation #lovingkindness #legacy #lifeline #thankyou #unforgettable #missyou

text:
________________________________________подари мне крылья, чтоб могла я летать,
над полями, лесами и не смела страдать.
ты возьми меня за руку,
нежно в ушко шепни:
- ты не бойся, с тобой я,
не расстанемся мы!
ну, а я вмиг поверю, так хотела сама,
и отдам всё на свете,
лишь бы знать, что нужна.
что не будет страданий,
и нет фальши и лжи,
лишь везде торжествует,
царство счастья, любви.
что вокруг окружает одна доброта,
и глаза засияют искрой нового дня.
снова сердце забьется, что его не унять,
мир тебе улыбнется, он всё сможет понять.
тихо скажет: живи и безумно люби!
а познавши любовь ты твори и твори!
только будет она, пусть взаимной любовь,
а иначе, зачем начинать тогда вновь?
дай мне крылья прошу, осчастливь ты меня,
без полета любви я не мыслю себя.
каждый сон я летаю, там я брежу тобой.
и всегда представляю, что ты мой, мой родной.
- где ты был столько лет? мне скажи не тая.
ну а ты вмиг ответишь: - я искал лишь тебя.
мы с тобой разожжем пламя жаркой любви,
будем вместе, вдвоем, только я, только ты,
и ни что и ни кто нам не сможет сказать,
потому, что мы любим, нас не смей осуждать.
потому что кто любит, тот способен летать!!!стихи.ру

#притча##праздник #счастье#любовь#семья #мысли#философия #высказывания#печаль #грусть#psyxogram#love #cool#metoo#доброеутро

text:
my words were born from despair.
they grew through adversity 
and matured through love.
love of god.
love of life.
love of self.
their existence hinges on both hurt and hope.
like yin and yang.
balanced.
both feed the ink that flows from my soul.
without one my words would die.
but like christ’s resurrection there was always hope to follow the hurt.
and despite the hurt hope rose.
my hurt did not bury me, it readied me for my own resurrection.
-raquel mccloud
...
sometimes i write paragraphs, sometimes i write poetry.
...
i write for me and i share my words for those that need to hear them. thank you for reading and sharing my words. thank you for being you. thank you for being here. 💕

text:
saw the fantabulous fringe wives club new show glittergrass last night. it was a brilliant, relevant, femtastic show. truly empowering. 
i then walked back to my car and noticed how relevant it was. it was a long, dark tree lined walk, i got a little nervy. i employed all my ‘survival’ tricks - keys in hand, walking in the middle of the road, pretending to chat on the phone (2am is a little late to chat to people really!). i even regretted my outfit choice ffs!!!!
i then realised all of these tricks are probably completely pointless if an attacker was really out there. 
it’s not right that women can’t walk home at night without fear, or like eurydice dixon sadly don’t make it home at all. 
so thanks to the fringe wives club and all other women (and men) who continue to highlight inequalities, and work to improve the lives of women and girls the world over. 
i dream that one day we can wear what we want, go where we want and all have equal opportunities. 
#fringewivesclub #glittergrass #glitteryclittery @fringewivesclub #feminism #walksafe #equality #metoo #lifelessordinary

text_retweet:
#repost @ndvhofficial (@get_repost)
・・・
“we have to re-educate ourselves to understand that unequivocally, every human being has the right to walk through this life with their full humanity in tact.” tarana burke is a survivor of sexual violence she faced as a child and a teenager. she credits her mother with providing her with an incredible amount of support through her healing process and encouraging her to be involved in activism. burke has worked with girls in marginalized communities since she was a teenager and continues to pioneer movements and advocate for girls and survivors of sexual violence. burke is most notably known for founding the “me too” movement which brought worldwide attention to the prevalence of gender based violence. tarana burke was a recipient of time magazine’s person of the year award in 2017. she currently serves as the senior director of girls for gender equity in brooklyn.  tarana burke continues to advocate for survivors by traveling the country to give talks about gender based violence and trauma. she stresses that both individuals and institutions must adopt an intersectional model to affect change. 
#metoo #blackhistorymonth #bhm #blackgirlmagic #blackwomenlead

text:
“our values are changing. it’s not just the final product anymore, finally the process matters.” maria clara roa cuorvo tells me as we discuss the slow food concept behind her restaurant @bastorestobar. 🌿 .

appropriately set in the luxurious @biohabitat.hotel where every detail has been thoughtfully designed to minimize impact and maximize mindfulness, basto is farm-to-table not because it’s a trend, but because it provides another opportunity for guests to deepen their awareness of the surrounding environment. by learning where their food comes from and how much prep went into each ingredient, diners @bastorestobar develop a newfound appreciation for the work behind a pretty plate. here chef clara picks herbs and edible flowers from the hotel orchard, as she does everyday with her perky garden assistant lula.

text:
✨ our theme for the month of march is all about men. 🙆🏽‍♂️ ⁣
⁣
in the midst of the #metoo movement and discussions about the social and economic mobility of ladies everywhere, men have become rather . . . vocal. 🗯while some are championing the female reformation (still a working title), others are pushing back against the wave of gender, racial and social reform -- coining the term #socialjusticewarrior to describe individuals who support social reform and civil rights movements. 🤦🏿‍♀️ ⁣
⁣
while some of you may disregard their tweets and comments as nothing but the ramblings of closeted (or proud) online racists, the rise of the very real alt-right and wall-centric viewpoints boiling across 🇺🇸 bring up some very uncomfortable questions about how we have (or haven't) defined our men (and women). ⁣
⁣
this month, we will be discussing a few think pieces about different male-centric issues and deconstructing some deeply rooted ideas about manhood through the lenses of film, social theories and superheroes.💪🏽 #wowandbeyond #ourworld  #sitinthemoment #manhood #callthebanners #allofthem #marchisformen #boyhood #masculinity

text:
#satnam #grateful to share more #heartchakravibes in my life.
today while sharing some of the #kundaliniyoga teachings with my recovering friend, a new student decided to join our little #sacredspace in time. she loved it! she opened up to me with a very personal & dangerous story.
i had to admit that i could not help her fix her life but, she could begin to create a new life for herself. a life filled with prayers, gratitude & health. if only she just be thankful for this moment. 
i just so happened to have a duplicate copy of my teacher @krishnakaur 's book, "i am a woman," so i gifted it to her. i told her, my teacher is already helping young women like you in los angeles. when you get better, you can too. i thought perhaps, if she saw someone who she could look up to, she will increase her chances of creating a more fulfilled life. #waheguru #yogibhajan #yogaforyouth #childrenarethefuture #celibacy #spiritualityforsex #metoo #riseup #sisepuede #despierta #latinxs #universal #uncoversantaana #createyourspace #divinefeminine #sednagong #kundalini #yoga #sacredgeometry #mentalhealth #ptsd

text:
leeds socialist workers party meeting for international women’s day! ‘women, resistance & revolution’. thursday 7 march, 7pm, swarthmore centre, woodhouse square, ls3 1ad. ￼trump to bolsonaro, the rise of the right means more misogyny and transphobia, along with racism.  millions of women and others who want to fight oppression have marched, protested and taken action – whether through the #metoo movement against sexual harassment, #timesup for equal pay, or through strikes like those in glasgow city council where women finally won their pay claim after 12 years of campaigning!  we have suffered eight years of tory austerity in britain, with women shouldering 85 percent of the burden of cuts in services and changes in welfare.  and as the pressure increases on families, government cuts have meant that many women’s refuges have been forced to close.  how can we turn the energy of the #metoo movement and people’s willingness to challenge sexist behaviour into a real challenge to the structural oppression faced by women in our society?  come to this meeting to discuss how women have fought back across the globe – and to celebrate the socialist tradition of fighting for women’s liberation.  #leedsswp #internationalwomensday ￼
￼
￼
￼ ￼

text: as i mentioned, over the coming weeks i’ll be posting some information about my children’s picture book “angel” and about some of the themes i wove into the book.  one of the main themes i wrote about was the issue of “denial”. this is not a particularly easy topic to talk about because let’s face it; we all do it to varying degrees.  whether it’s about how many drinks we’re having after the kids go to bed, how much money we’re spending online or even denying our feelings for the sake of a relationship, none of us can honestly say we are true to ourselves 100% of the time.  whilst these examples might sound relatively harmless, when it comes to “big” denial, like in the case of sexual abuse, this is where it tends to polarise people and bring out very strong reactions.  as a society we have become expert at pointing the finger of blame and labelling people who we deem “inappropriate” or not living up to our expectations or standards.  online bullying and trolling are very good examples of this.  now, i am not for a moment saying that i condone the behaviour of adults who turn a blind eye to sexual abuse.  what i am saying, is that denial happens and it happens often, particularly in the case of trans-generational sexual abuse.  denial happens for myriad reasons and purposes.  what i am suggesting is rather than get stuck in the “blame and shame”, let’s just say, “okay denial happens.  but what can we do about it?” it is then, and only then, that we may get somewhere in terms of the horrific statistics that tell us that 1 in 3 girls and 1 in 7 boys will be either sexually abused or sexually assaulted by the time the reach 18.  if we are to be outraged by anything, be outraged by those statistics.  what we are doing as a society is not working.  we must look at things differently.  looking at the issue of denial is a start in the right direction. #teachersfollowteachers #teachersofinstagram #childadvocate #divinefeminine #divinemasculine #healing #truth #protectourkids #sexualabuse #metoo #domesticviolence

text:
read morgan's blog post about tools for change. this workshop is an initiative to give students an opportunity to learn about what you can do to prevent and challenge beliefs surrounding sexualized violence. "upon first hearing about the workshop, i was both incredibly excited and slightly confused.

i was excited because this is giving students the ability to act and actually do something about some of the current sexualized issues in the world which movements such as #metoo have begun to address.

i was confused because although i had heard the terms “sexual harassment” and “sexual assault” before, i had never heard the term sexualized violence and i, as many of the other participants in the workshop, was not quite sure what it meant." want to read more? check the link in our profile!
name: University of Victoria
tweet_full:
read morgan's blog post about tools for change. this workshop is an initiative to give students an opportunity to learn about what you can do to prevent and challenge beliefs surrounding sexualized violence. "upon first hearing about the workshop, i was both incredibly excited and slightly confused.

i was excited because this is giving students the ability to act and actually do something about some of the current sexualized issues in the world which movements such as #metoo have begun to address.

i was confused because although i had heard the terms “sexual harassment” and “sexual assault” before, i had never heard the term sexualized violence and i, as many of the other participants in the workshop, was not quite sure what it meant." want to read more? check the link in our profile!

text:
‼️‼️i don’t give a fuck how a female dresses. she is *never* “asking for it”‼️‼️ apparently now, showing your nipples is an open invitation for men to grab your boobs without your consent? and to harass you and make you feel like an object? 🤔 if i can contain myself around you, why can’t you do the same for me? i’ve experienced endless sexual harassment in my life and never once did i want it. never once did i put on my shirt without a bra, hoping that a man would grab my chest without asking.

it’s just so fucking sad that we live in a society where women are so unbelievably degraded every single day. i could wear a sexy ass outfit or a god damn hefty trash bag and i would still get objectified. in court, they’ll ask you what you wore when you tell them you got raped. even our own government normalizes this fucked up type of behavior?
————————————————
“you shouldn’t of wore that, that’s why they did that to you” “you’re a slut for showing your nipples” “you can’t dress like that and expect men not to say stuff”
————————————————
the point here is, that what a woman wears, should never determine how much respect you give her. and it certainly should never determine her worth as a person. bodies are just fucking bodies!!! why do we make them such a big deal? the female body is so fucking sexualized to the point where you’re damned if you do, damned if you don’t. you wanna feel good and embrace your beautiful body? fuck that, you’re a whore! you wanna be modest and keep to yourself? fuck that, you’re a prude! 
do you know how hard it can be to get dressed when you have to always consider this? am i being too much? am i covered up enough? (when it reality none of this should matter) 
but this is exactly why i choose to just wear/do whatever the fuck i want, because it’s always a losing battle in today’s society. i truly lose hope for society when i think deeply about this topic. i lose hope when i think about all the “men” who have wrongfully touched my body without my consent, because of “how i was dressed.” but at the end of the day, i’d much rather dress however the hell i please - than cover up to try and avoid the inevitable degradation of my body. ❣️ #metoo

text_retweet:
‘i had repressed the dream as soon as i woke up, scared of focusing on it or remembering it too well. i thought if i didn’t think of it, i would forget, as one does with most normal dreams. but, these dreams are not normal, no matter how much my body may try to convince me so. they are ugly and they are violent; they feel normal only in this nightmarish reality of being a survivor in an ongoing rape culture.’ from the new piece on mundane nightmares from @tacriona. sometimes nightmares aren’t all ghouls and goblins, or giant 🐝 like in this picture (2017 #35mm ) - sometimes they’re just the realities of a sometimes nightmarish reality. ••
the photograph on the article (of the lamp) is very private and holds a lot of weight for me. please don’t re-use it, even if you’re reposting. ••
[id: a wall in london with graffiti art of two big honey bees]

text:
‘into the dark’ has a #metoo moment with the jimmi simpson-starring ‘treehouse’ – tv insider
#
preview aaron epstein/hulu "treehouse," the latest installment of into the dark, hulu's series of macabre, standalone stories, serves up a frightening, timely tale for the #metoo era. peter rake (westworld's jimmi simpson, above, with onscreen daughter kylie rogers), a well-known tv chef, "has been in a position of power and abused it," executive producer and star julianna guill explains of the sexual predator. "he has never considered how his behavior impacts those around him." until he flees town. following some allegations made against him, he heads to his family's secluded villa. on his way, the father and divorcé stops at a bait shop and meets a group of women (played by guill, mary mccormack and stephanie beatriz, among others) in a bachelorette party. let's just say things get witchy from there — and guill's musician kara, the most recent object of peter's flirtation, is a major part of it all. "she's the most emotionally affected," guill teases. the big question, though, according to the producer, is "can [peter] make a change, or is he going to continue in this pattern of behavior?" and does he even deserve the chance? ﻿ into the dark, "treehouse," episode premiere, friday, march 1, hulu…

preview aaron epstein/hulu "treehouse," the latest installment of into the dark, hulu's series of macabre, standalone stories, serves up a frightening, timely tale for the #metoo era. peter rake (westworld's jimmi simpson, above, with onscreen daughter kylie rogers), a well-known tv chef, "has been in a position of power and abused it," executive producer and star julianna guill explains of the sexual predator. "he has never considered how his behavior impacts those around him." until he flees town. following some allegations made against him, he heads to his family's secluded villa. on his way, the father and divorcé stops at a bait shop and meets a group of women (played by guill, mary mccormack and stephanie beatriz, among others) in a bachelorette party. let's just say things get witchy from there — and guill's musician kara, the most recent object of peter's flirtation, is a major part of it all. "she's the most emotionally affected," guill teases. the big question, though, according to the producer, is "can [peter] make a change, or is he going to continue in this pattern of behavior?" and does he even deserve the chance? ﻿ into the dark, "treehouse," episode premiere, friday, march 1, hulu…

text:
i've been working on a new book project about boys.  the ever unfolding shitshow of the trump/ kavanaugh/ #metoo era has been a wakeup call to something deeply rotten in our society- a genuine systemic problem in the way that men are allowed to behave.  i have three boys of my own.  three kindhearted, sweet, sometimes thoughtful, sometimes rambunctious, occasionally obnoxious boys, aged 8, 5 and 1.  do i believe that they will inevitably, due to some toxic soup of 'brain sex' and testosterone and mars-ness grow up to be enthusiastic members of the putrid patriarchy?  i do not.  i honestly believe that they have the same innate capacity for empathy and kindness and gentleness and writing thank you letters and loading the dishwasher as anyone born in a female body.  i believe that an unbelievable amount of rubbish has been spouted about brain sex and gender essentialism that is damaging to all. 
what i do believe is that despite my best efforts, in infinite and often quite subtle ways, they are receiving very different socialization than their female peers.  the tv shows, and games and books that are heavily marketed towards them almost always lack any significant emotional content or complexity and almost always feature battles or fighting in some way or another.  the standard main character of a boys middle grade or early reader fiction book tends to be a disaffected pre-teen who hates school, girls and the sound of his boring nagging mom.  it's depressing and sexist and nihilistic.  it's a stretch to draw a straight line from horrid henry to the stanford rapist, but i believe there is something in there that needs addressing.
so it's great to see the bright spots in all this.  last week i took my 8 year old to hear @juddwinick talk about his new #hilo book and he was lovely and life affirming and fun and drew an individual cartoon in everyone's book.  there were around 30 young boys there and they were articulate and engaged and funny and asked great questions.  it was a delight to see.  is anyone else a bit bored of the nihilism and normalization of being an arsehole in boys books? what other books do you recommend for pre-teen boys? #boymom #momofboys #t

text:
day 28 of #authorlifemonth. the last one: what’s next.  #screenqueens releases june 11 and here’s a sneak peek. this book and the #stemgirls in it are quite special to me.
.
it will be my first published contemporary.
.
it marks a new publisher in the amazingness that is @penguinteen @razorbillbooks.
.
it is my first time writing multiple points of view characters (i may never go back!).
.
it is about young women dealing with a world that’s been slow to change to accept them but that needs to for it’s the future. it’s a world of #stem that i never had the confidence to enter. and that was okay because i was a girl. no one expected me to excel in math and science and it became a self-fulfilling prophecy. i’m proud of the #womenintech and #womenwhocode who are forging a road i didn’t think was open to me and in this time of #metoo they are opening doors for all the girls who i hope will read this book and see themselves.
.
thanks to everyone for following along with this february of a look at my #authorlife and to @missdahlelama for hosting it. now: back to work on the next one.

text:
ever wonder why am i still here ! 
why have i had to endure these lies, the hate, the rumors... god why haven’t you released me from this yet? 
god doesn’t promise to take you out of the problems. 
but he does promise to walk you through them. 
he does promise to give you strength. 
and if you walk faithfully to what he has called you to do, and how to act... he will prepare a feast for you right before your enemies! 
you don’t have to try to defend yourself. 
you don’t have to prove yourself. 
you don’t have to fight back. 
you don’t have to work harder. 
you don’t have to seek revenge. 
you don’t have to hold onto hate. 
you don’t have to withhold forgiveness. 
instead... walk the way god calls you to. 
show love, and be love... period 
as you focus on that... god goes to bat for you. 
he brings darkness into light... and you better believe he will restore all that was stolen from you. 
be encouraged today. 
forgive. 
walk in peace and love 
and know god is working behind the scenes preparing your feast !!!

text:
#reflectionsofarawfooddetox #rawvegan
#because someone needed the motivation today and because i needed a reminder how far i’ve come along this journey. 
november 18, 2013 marked one year, one month, and four days after i had experienced one of the most horrific events in my life on october 15th, 2012. maybe one day i’ll have the courage to share my story, #metoo, but for now this is about how i’ve evolved since then. depression, anger, frustration, why me, hurt, anxiety, hostility, self blame, hatred, unbelievable hatred, and regret were just a few of the things that the woman on the left of each pic was feeling. that day i took those pics with no idea in my mind that my journey would lead me here but it did. to say i’m in a much different and better place would be an understatement. do i still have work to do? of course, much needed shadow work to purge the remainder of some of the aforementioned emotions, that once plagued me, above; but the me now is so very thankful for the me then who overcame so much shit that even i’m in awe. tears want to flow as i type this because that girl was a wreck. a train wreck wanting to end it all but i refused to be beaten. i refused to be shut down. i refused to be ran over. i refused to rollover and die for those who wanted it. so i rose from the ashes. i rose from being burned. i rose from that train wreck to become who i am today. 
when i look in the mirror some days i see so many flaws but then my spirit, my oversoul, checks me fiercely with no apologies to remind me of just how very beautiful i am. today she guided me to go back some years and create this comparison; to reminisce for a brief moment; to look at the collection of my scars and admire them for what they represent........#victory #triumph #strength #tenacity #perseverance #excellence 
if you’re reading this and you’re ready to quit know that i was too so very very very very very very very very very very very very very very very very very very many times but i knew i was better than quitting and so are you. love yourself enough to keep going #dontquit #thisis42yearsold #aginggracefully #wiser #leveledallthewayup2019 #cont. below 👇🏾👇🏾
#swipe 👉🏾👉🏾

text:
i confessed to her
i hadn’t been sleeping well,
i hardly do anyways.
even with the door
closed and locked.
even with the
light on and music
playing nonstop.
.
she asked why,
what did i dream of?
.
i admitted,
it was the same
reoccurring nightmare,
the one of him raping me.
and no matter what i did
i could never escape his hands,
his words.
i could never escape
him.
.
she laughed,
telling me not to drink so much water
before bed.
.
.
.
#ljlafleur #wherethornsmeetspetals #wheretwooceansmeet #copyright #photography #womenaremagic #wherecloudsreside #wherestarshide
.
day four of the flu, bare with me on this post.
.
this is a reminder that as you’re healing, the one person who will have your back is yourself. don’t rely on others to understand your pain because most of them can’t fathom the idea of something so incredibly awful happening to them, let alone to someone they know. they do not have the capacity to grasp the hurt you are working through or have worked through.
.
i’m so proud of how far you’ve come, that you’re not giving up. i’m proud of how much you’ve healed up to this point. you’re a fighter, you’re an incredibly beautiful soul because of that reason alone.
.
keep progressing, and when you feel like you have no fight left...breathe. continue doing so until you’re ready to stand up again. i believe in you, love.
.
#healyourselfwhole
.
#heart #poem #poetry #poetrycommunity #writingcommunity #writing #adventure #poetryofinstagram #poet #healing #metoo #journey #selflove #selfworth #selfcare #warrior #queen #music #traveling
