text:
la psicoterapia humanista te permite profundizar en tus conflictos personales, poner conciencia en las dificultades y desarrollar tus propios recursos para afrontarlas.

el objetivo es integrar todos los aspectos de tu personalidad, con el fin de que llegues a ser quién eres, en lugar de que pretendas ser quién no eres: quién que te gustaría ser, o quién crees que deberías ser.

es un proceso impulsado por tu voluntad de ver y tu voluntad de sanar. una oportunidad para que, de forma activa y responsable, explores los problemas que aparecen en tu vida.

la relación terapéutica humanista:

una de las características de la psicoterapia humanista es la actitud: empática, con coherencia, autenticidad, conciencia y responsabilidad. esta es la base para que el encuentro interpersonal se convierta en una relación terapéutica. 
la presencia de la terapeuta te proporciona un espacio seguro, en el que puedes poner palabras a lo que te sucede y sentir cómo te afecta.

la terapeuta no te dirige con consejos, interpretaciones o pautas de modificación de conducta, sino que te apoya y te acompaña en el proceso que estás viviendo.

te escucha sin juicios ni valoraciones, y profundiza junto a ti en los problemas, respetando tu propio ritmo.te acompaña en los momentos difíciles, mientras exploras tus emociones, recursos y creencias, y encuentras tu propio significado a lo que te sucede. te señala lo que forma parte de tu experiencia presente, y que tú, por ti mismo, no eres capaz de ver. te apoya para que, al poner conciencia en lo que haces y en cómo y para qué lo haces, puedas descubrir aspectos de ti mismo que te mantienen en una situación de sufrimiento, desarrolles tus capacidades personales y encuentres tu propia forma de resolverlo, cambiarlo o aceptarlo.🌹#psicologíafemenia #psicología #filosofía #ser #sermujer #reflexión #meditaciones #yoga #mindfulness #namaste #amor #amorpropio #vida #abundancia #feminidad #feminista #feminismo #femenina #mujer #metoo #moonmother #meditación #meditaciones #yoni #diosa #bruja #hechicera

text:
yesterday marked the second year anniversary since starting monthly benlysta infusions. while it’s not a cure, and despite the toll immunosuppressants take on my body, i’m super grateful for this treatment option.
🥳
taking the next few days to rest, and reminding myself, i’m not wasting my entire day doing nothing, i’m doing exactly what i need to do: recovering.
😷

yeah. yikes. -

text:
*periodistas de maicao participaron en la transformación cultural, bajo el taller " la noticia y perspectiva de género*" con el objetivo de promover la equidad de genero y rechazar la discriminación y violencia de toda índole contra las mujeres del municipio, la comisaria de maicao, la defensoría del pueblo y la fundación identidad multiverso, en el marco de la fecha internacional de la mujer propicio un espacio de reflexión con los periodistas de maicao  para el análisis y el manejo de esterotipos, y poder transformar cultura con el taller la noticia y  perspetiva de género.

siguenos en la ruta de dialogo intercultural de los derechos de la mujer étnica. 🎙identidad la voz de la mujer colombia stereo. 103.7 fm todos los sábados de 7: 30 am.

text:
danny and i have been diving deep individually on our spiritual journeys but also into our relationship with each other. ⁣
⁣
we are working on connecting on an even deeper level of intimacy through our mental & emotional connections. ⁣
⁣
we are slowing down with each other to date again, to stare into each other’s eyes, to notice each other in the silence, to have real conversations that go beyond the surface level ish, to hold each other with passion...and other things not appropriate for social media at this time. 🙃⁣
⁣
it’s been so beautiful and inspiring. ⁣
we are seeing each other with fresh eyes. ⁣
⁣
i’m stepping into my divine feminine role and no longer claiming the unbalanced masculine that i lived in my whole life. ⁣
⁣
i couldn’t feel more grateful that i have a husband that’s willing to do the hard work in life and our relationship to grow. 😭♥️⁣

text:
katie mckenzie bring her love and passion to one of our panels next week for this year's women's awareness week #iwd2019 in vancouver. .
.
.
katie’s life has been a journey that has moved, shifted, changed, contracted and expanded.  this journey is what brought katie to her passion for movement.  movement has been her safe haven since before she can remember, without even knowing, katie went through movement regardless of the state she was in.  when katie was lost, when she was found, when she was happy, when she was sad - katie needed to move. this passion grew when she became a mother.  katie realized that the way that she perceived herself was not how she wanted the world to see themselves, and that self-love through compassion, kindness and breath is what brings true internal love and strength.
.
.
after the birth of her first child, katie shifted the way she moved and received her pilates certification, deepened her pre and post natal knowledge and adjusted her personal practice to safely and lovingly move her body.  during katie’s pregnancy with her second child, she was diagnosed with perinatal and then post-partum depression. katie found the practice of qi gong - which deepened her body and soul connection.  the desire to understand how the body moves, stands and connects at its best found katie seeking a deeper knowledge.  through that desire, katie was led to the consultation of pelvic floor physiotherapists, rmt's and chiropractors to further strengthen her body and soul alignment practice, which drastically impacts the practice that she now leads for others. .
.
all of this led to the creation of the block and the release. two mat movement practices katie teaches, most recently at the beautiful shared workspace werklab in vancouver, but katie can always be found at her home away from home at lagree west as the master lead trainer. .
.
katie will be hosting a special back to back lagree west program for charity with minibar canada and vancouver women's health collective on march 10 4:00pm & 5:15pm - open to all humans/all genders.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10) link in @minibarcanada’s profile.

text:
een bulgaar, een oekraïense en een nederlander, zet ze samen op het podium en je krijgt in combinatie van persoonlijke ervaringen/verhalen uit het publiek een prachtige en intense voorstelling. over de magie in je leven houden, respect en ouder worden.
playback theater heeft een hele belangrijke plek in mijn leven. als professional, maar ook heb ik als publiek tijdens een voorstelling op de vertellersstoel ervaren wat het kan geven. mijn diepste geheim is daar naar boven gekomen. een beerput geopend, een hels proces met een waanzinnige transformatie. ik hen mezelf opnieuw gevonden en daarmee in expressie expert geboren. #expressieexpert #playbacktheatre #vertrouweninjezelf #havethegutstoexpressyourself #storytelling #metoo

text:
someone once told me to never talk about my sexual assault, to never bring it up again as it’s in the past and just forget about it and move on.
.
if only it were that simple!
.
the physical assault may have been a year ago but the effects of it still remains in my present. almost like that of an earthquake, the earthquake has stopped but there are after shocks but will eventually stop and return to its new normal. .
as more people are finding out about my assault, as i am vocal and will not be anything but, they are approaching me with disbelief, questioning why i didn’t act a certain way, why i didn’t call the police in that very moment.
.
in honesty, this is something no survivor wants to hear. no survivor wants to justify their actions or why they did or did not react the way they did.
.
be mindful, be polite, if you don’t get it it is clear you are not a survivor.
.
don’t judge a situation that you were not in.
.
#metoo #metoomovement #sexualassault #sexualassaultsurvivor #survivor #fitmom #fitfam #fitstagram #fitnessjourney #gym #gymismysavinggrace #imsavingmylife #notavictim

text: i actually cried when @taranajaneen entered the room today, her presence is so powerful and her work is life changing. it was such a privilege to hear her speak this morning on her history with domestic violence and abuse, how she came to create the #metoo movement, and how we can all be better advocates for survivors in promoting healing and creating systemic change. our country is better because of people like tarana who have the courage to speak up about traumatic personal experiences in order to create change. palm beach county is better because of the work of avda and their commitment to assisting survivors. it’s on all of us to end the cycle of abuse for the generations of the future. ❤️

text:
posting this to remind myself this is my forever mood because i almost forgot this week.

self love and self care as a woman is a radical political act in a world where we are constantly subjected to relentless male gaze and impossible standards. so just know that i’m always going to be feeling myself no matter what. 
when i was young i was too boyish to be considered valuable, now i’m older i’m too pretty to be considered smart. you know what? fuck all y’all. 
i’m not going to be what you want so you can keep your damn opinions to yourself. don’t tell me to smile. don’t tell me i’m beautiful when i’m talking to you about business. don’t shout at me in the street.

don’t feel it’s ok to harass me because i’m an entrepreneur who doesn’t have an hr department to report you to. 
and no you can’t touch my fucking hair either.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#selfcareisaradicalact #timesup #metoo #womeninbusiness #matriarchynow #fuckthepatriarchy #selflove #weshouldallbefeminists 
#explore #explorepage #blackownedbusiness #independentbusiness

text: this woman right here colors my world!!! i had the complete honor of being mentored by this beautiful woman in my first year at mops nearly 5 years ago. it feels like i’ve known her for a lifetime. she knows such intimate details of my life and i of hers. the greatest quality i look for in a friend is vulnerability - and she is just that, paired with wisdom, and grace and love. her heart to serve others inspires me to love harder, and to love bigger. i’ve missed her so since we moved away but she has consistently sent me the sweetest messages at random that made me know i am still in her heart. how did i deserve that spot? it’s beyond me, but i’m so grateful to be there. she has residence in my heart as well. love this woman soooo much! everyone needs a barbara in their life. i’m grateful god brought her into mine. ♥️♥️♥️

text:
there is never a "right" time to make a big change in your life.⠀
⠀
it will always feel scary, uncomfortable. ⠀
⠀
you will be afraid of what people think. ⠀
⠀
you will be nervous about what others think. ⠀
⠀
will you fail? did you make the right choice? ⠀
⠀
all of that is normal.⠀
⠀
i am here to help you. you can be more than what you have let yourself be. you are powerful.⠀

text:
thrilled to welcome anna farrant's energy and ethos to the panel for this year's women's awareness week for #iwd2019 in vancouver. .
.
anna farrant co-founded all city athletics with jordan bowers in 2012! all city is a boutique boxing fitness brand that offers group fitness classes to those who want to train like a fighter!  anna started boxing in 2008 as a way to relieve stress from work and fell in love with the sport which is one of the most challenging, and arguably therapeutic, workouts possible. her training philosophy is “your mind will give out before your body does” reminding her clients that boxing is not only physical but will make you mentally strong. her goal is to make boxing fun and accessible to those who may not have the desire to step in the ring while still keeping it authentic!
.
.
as well as speaking on our well beings panel, march 4; anna will be hosting a special boxing 101 class for charity with minibar canada the vancouver women's health collective on march 9 2:00pm. this fitness class is open to all humans/all genders.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)
https://iwd2019vancouver.eventbrite.ca or the link in @minibarcanada's profile.

text: får väldigt mkt frågor ifrån media och på sociala medier ifall jag fått mkt negativ kritik för det jag gör av just män. men det jag fått i respons av män (ca 1/3 av alla som skriver) är totala motsatsen!! (det är totalt 2-3 st som män/kvinnor som uttalat sig negativt) de män som gett sin åsikt är så innerligt tacksamma över att jag öppet berättar om detta, de ifrågasätter inte det jag blev/blir utsatt för eller ifrågasätter ”hur farligt det eg var”. de stöttar, backar upp och tar ställning i frågan och drar ofta paralleller till om det hände deras #döttrar / #dotter #systrar #mammor #tjejkompisar. att detta sker är rätt unikt i dessa frågor! men vi har fortfarande en lång väg kvar i denna fråga... om alla män öppet tog ställning - på #sociala medier, på #jobbet i diskussioner med #vänner när skämten dras på #förfest :en eller #gym #gym :et då deras #killkompisar klagar då de alltid får tjata för att få #ligga. då tror jag mycket skulle hända... ni #män behövs så otroligt mycket i detta, att ni ifrågasätter #sexualbrottslagstiftning :en  och polisens utredningar i dessa fall, deras bemötande av #brottsoffer som blivit utsatta för övergrepp mm. jag är så innerligt tacksam för allt #stöd jag fått av er❤️ ni starka, säkra män, involvera era manliga vänner och kämpa så att vi tillsammans kan se till att ingen mer #tjej / #barn / #kvinna / #man någonsin blir utsatt igen. tillsammans kan vi se till att ingen någonsin vågar/kan #våldta igen!! tack för att ni finns🙏 att tex anders lindeberg på if själv kontaktar media och uttalar sig om utredningen och det falska pm som #larshagewald hos @polisen i västerås skickat till #jesperrundeberg visar hur viktiga ni är i denna kamp!!!@vasterasmotsexuellaovergrepp #förjenny #backajenny #feministisktperspektiv #metoo #metoosweden #metoomovement #metoo❤️ @hannabergwall

text:
many entrepreneurs are stymied by the question: how am i actually different from the competition? we know it’s essential to identify a “unique selling proposition,” but in a competitive marketplace where it seems everything’s been done, it can sometimes be hard to articulate your specific value.

3yrs ago adding a bespoke tailor to my staff who is actually a cutter,  a craft that is quickly disappearing , it put my barbershop brand on another level and adding a mindset therapist this new year continues to widen the gap between other competing barbershops.

leverage your personality. don’t become part of the crowd.
i’m constantly asking people regardless of their level of position if they’re having fun making a difference. for me, this is my personality. i want to make a difference, but i want to have fun along the way.

text:
the first woman to ever look me in the eye and say “you don’t have to do anything you don’t want to” was a stripper. “pay her what you owe her” a dancer i didn’t know demanded for me once. “they have to listen to you”
“you set the prices not them”
“you can use your heel to kick him and run away”  a million refused lap dances and drinks tossed in rude faces, a thousand crying hugs and giving girls rides. pizza after work on nights you need to feel human. “don’t touch her without permission” portia would say e v e r y time.  because instead of empty promises of “if anyone touches you i’ll kill them”, the women you work with often act in the moment. and it comes up from her belly, hot with fire spewing from her mouth for you, and everyone before and after you. because she is you, and then all you can do to repay her is to spew your fire like a dragon and light the way #yesastripper #sexworkiswork #sexworkersrightsarehumanrights #metoo

text:
i've had some stupendous momentous news in my sexual harassment complaint with the labour party. 
having originally claimed that my case was a complete fabrication, my harassar upon seeing my evidence withdrew from the complaint procedure altogether, refusing to engage in it any further. 
i was afraid that that was the end and there would be no justice, but i'm so pleased and just so relieved to say that the ncc have ruled in my favour and expelled him from the labour party.

i'm quite emotional right now but so relieved. i have so many criticisms to make of the whole sexual harassment procedure, which i will do another time but right now i just want to hug and kiss everybody!
#metoo #timesup #womeninpolitics #labourparty

text:
bureau strikt is de bedrijfsnaam waaronder petra vervoort op freelance basis werkzaam is op het gebied van omgangsvormen en integriteit.

u kunt bij bureau strikt terecht voor:
• opstellen en/of actualiseren van goed psa- en integriteitsbeleid
• externe vertrouwenspersoon voor werknemers bij een melding op het gebied van psycho sociale arbeidsbelasting
• begeleiding van de aangeklaagde werknemer*
• externe vertrouwenspersoon bij het melden van het vermoeden van een misstand (integriteit)
• het management adviseren en ondersteunen over een juridisch en communicatief juiste procedure bij een crisissituatie
• coördinator/vraagbaak interne vertrouwenspersonen
• begeleiding intervisie interne vertrouwenspersonen
• thema workshops, zoals het bespreken van jurisprudentie,  bewustwording rond pesten of integriteit • artikelen / blogs, toegespitst op een actueel thema binnen de organisatie *het begeleiden van een aangeklaagde gebeurt in de praktijk nog niet zo vaak. bij simpelere klachten, is het ook niet nodig. bij ernstigere zaken (seksuele intimidatie, misbruik, ernstige pestklachten enz.) heeft het een enorme meerwaarde wanneer ook degene tegen wie de klacht is gericht wordt ondersteund tijdens het klachttraject. deze meerwaarde betreft alle betrokken partijen: de melder/klager, de aangeklaagde en de organisatie.

ik ben gecertificeerd bij de landelijke vereniging voor vertrouwenspersonen (lvv) onder nummer 101018
https://www.lvvv.nl/

meer informatie? kijk op https://bureaustrikt.nl/ of neem contact op met info@bureaustrikt.nl

text:
ik keek gisterenavond op npo3 naar verschillende programma's over carnaval en besefte me toen dat 'de rest van nederland' (lees; iedereen boven de rivieren) vast naar ons moet kijken alsof we hier in het zuiden niet goed wijs zijn 🤣 als je er van een afstandje naar kijkt is dat natuurlijk ook zo 😜
als je er middenin woont ook trouwens... brabantse gezelligheid 😊
.
.
zelf ben ik wel opgegroeid met carnaval, dat kan niet anders in een 100% brabantse familie, maar vier ik het al jaren niet meer. heel lang heb ik niet goed beseft waarom niet maar sinds ik weet (én accepteer!) dat ik hoogsensitief ben valt eigenlijk alles op zijn plaats. want hoe gezellig ik het hossen, het bier drinken en de ontzettend foute carnavalsliedjes ook vind; het zijn echt veel te veel prikkels. daar moet ik zo lang van bijkomen dat het de moeite niet waard is. .
.
het wordt dus een heerlijk rustig weekend voor mij 😉 waarbij ik het feestgedruis zoveel mogelijk probeer te ontlopen. 
waarschijnlijk een perfecte gelegenheid om die pan erwtensoep te maken deze winter nu het nog kan. .
.
op de foto trouwens geen erwtensoep maar het broodje buikspek van afgelopen weekend. mét zelfgemaakte stoombroodjes naar recept van @bysam 👌 ik maakte ze in de stoomoven en dat ging perfect.
.
.
ben jij #teamcarnaval of #teamdoemaarnormaal ? .
.
#carnaval #brabant #tilburg #buikspek #hsp #hoogsensitief #baconlover  #momofukuporkbuns #stoombroodje #stoomoven #zelfgemaaktisleuker

text:
last but definitely not least, for my black history month posts🚨

tarana burke (born september 12, 1973) is a civil rights activist from the bronx, new york who founded the me too movement. in 2006, burke began using the phrase "me too" to raise awareness of the pervasiveness of sexual abuse and assault in society, and the phrase developed into a broader movement, following the 2017 use of #metoo as a hashtag following the harvey weinstein sexual abuse allegations. time named burke, among a group of other prominent activists dubbed "the silence breakers", as the time person of the year for 2017. burke attends public speaking events across the country and is currently senior director at girls for gender equity in brooklyn. learn more about @taranajaneen  @wikipedia

text:
escrevo e reescrevo essa história na minha cabeça. a minha história. a minha vida. a minha dor. escrevo. apago. esqueço. me esforço pra esquecer. depois me esforço pra lembrar. não aguento. dói. sangra. eu quero me libertar dessa carga. minha alma sempre foi tão pesada. sempre senti não pertencer a mim. não pertencer a esse corpo. sei lá. me sinto presa. sabe, eu me sinto como se não merecesse as coisas. não mereço nada. não mereço ser feliz. não me permito ser. me saboto.  eu quero contar a minha história. um grupo seleto de pessoas a conhece em partes. sinto vontade de gritá-la pro mundo. mas dessa vez eu quero contar uma história sem vilões, sem anti heróis. sem ódio. sem desejo de vingança. será possível?  tento entender o que leva as pessoas a serem tão cruéis, manipuladoras, e abusadoras. são pessoas ruins? na cabeças delas, o que elas pensam? será que pensam? são doentes? também precisam de ajuda? fazer o que fazem seriam pedidos de ajuda? têm consciência do mal que fazem? o que é o mal? o que é bem? todos buscam a felicidade? o que é felicidade? afinal, qual o objetivo disso tudo? há sentido? quais são as verdadeiras regras desse jogo?
contar a história, nua e crua, do jeito que sai, já quase custou a minha vida. será que eles merecem tanto? minha vida como um troféu pra tantas barbaridades? a minha vida é o que tenho de mais precioso, mas sinto que ela nunca pertenceu a mim mesma... "é preciso paz pra poder sorrir"

text:
“tell the story of the mountain you climbed. your words could become a page in someone else's survival guide.” morgan harper nichols.
.
.
life is completely unpredictable, things that you never thought were possible happen.
. 
asking for help & healing is possible too, we all heal in different ways
.
whether it's having a therapist, taking medication, practice meditation,  or practicing spirituality, etc. no one is out there to judge you for the way you care for yourself or for any of the crap you’ve gone through...
.
check on each other, for the days when you are anxious or depressed, struggling to cope with something going on, or having a bad day, you don't have to go through it alone — 
to whoever needs to hear this, my door is always open, my phone is always on & my dm’s are always available ... 💕
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#metoo #selflove #quotes #fitfam #comeasyouare #healthylifestyle #supportivefriends

text:
meine freundin @yvemey und ihr freund ziehen in kürze um. da ein bekannter von ihnen eine wohnung sucht und sie einen nachmieter für die alten vier wände, organisierte sie vor ein paar tagen für ihn eine wohnungsführung. er stellte viele fragen zur wohnung - nur das "vertragliche" wollte er dann lieber mit dem herrn des hauses besprechen. 
und ich muss sagen: zu recht. da meine #freundin nämlich eine frau ist, kann sie zunächst einmal nicht besonders gut lesen. äääh... welcher buchstabe kommt nochmal nach b? juristische sprache, wie sie in verträgen genutzt wird, macht für sie keinen sinn. #mietrecht verwechselt sie mit #metoo und zählen kann sie nur bis fünf. wieviel miete kostet? also... so ungefähr fünf. selbst, wenn sie den #mietvertrag lesen und verstehen könnte, hätte sie ihm nicht weiterhelfen können, denn niemals hätte sie ihn in der für sie viel zu komplizierten dokumentenablage - oder überhaupt die ablage an sich - gefunden, solange die sich weder in der #küche, noch in ihrem #schminktäschchen befindet. und am ende interessieren sie vertragsangelegenheiten auch gar nicht. ich meine, hat sie als #frau überhaupt das recht, immobilien zu mieten oder gar zu erwerben? schließlich haben wir ja schon beim wahlrecht gesehen, wohin es führt, wenn #frauen plötzlich dieselben rechte bekommen wie #männer. chaos auf den straßen. und man würde schließlich auch keine frau nach ihrer politischen meinung fragen - denn die hat sie, wenn überhaupt, eh von ihrem mann übernommen.
meine #freundin aber war zur #revolution aufgelegt. sie holte den vertrag hervor und gab die vertraglichen informationen weiter. es ist nicht überliefert, ob besagter bekannte inzwischen aus dem koma erwacht ist.
.
#feminismus #feminism #feministin #equality #gleichberechtigung #igotpussy #diskriminierung #vorurteile #stereotypes

text:
sobre el beso forzado a diego boneta. voy a hacer mi comentario sobre este tema.. quizás un poco tardío pero creo q es necesario.. hace rato me viene dando vuelta en mi cabeza, el porque nuestra televisión está en picada, el porque la internet, y sobretodo netflix nos ha quitado público y siempre llegó al mismo pensamiento..
como profesional de las comunicaciones puedo decir con toda propiedad que hace rato que nuestra televisión perdió el respeto por el otro ; veo como en matinales, en backstage los periodistas y o conductores no respetan al que tienen al frente. no los dejan contestar, no respetan su metro cuadrado, son desconsiderado  haciéndose los lindos o las  lindas y sobajeando  o robando piquitos a gente que en realidad esta mostrando su arte... lo veo en entrevistas, lo veo en este caso. lo veo a diario.  lo veo en todas partes..
nos falta consideración .. el otro es un artista y como tal debe ser respetado.
el otro es una persona y como tal debe ser respetado.
si; esta en un evento público, tratando de ser agradable y entrar en el juego de la entrevista, pero  porque no mantener los límites, porque no respetar su metro cuadrado?
si; para mi esto es acoso..
una desconsideración tremenda de una mujer hacia un hombre.
para mi esta es una de las razones de porque cada día la tv abierta pierde credibilidad y buen gusto.. se me viene a la cabeza las alfombras rojas de cuanto oscar haya y el flirteo ente george clooney y giuliana depandi en la tv.
era un juego mediático? si.
estaban los dos de acuerdo? si.
ella alguna vez traspaso el límite y se le tiro encima al reconocido actor? nunca!, porque?  porque ella es una tremenda periodista, profesional pero por sobretodo eso, respetuosa del  trabajo y de la persona a la cual  estaba entrevistando. ella le dio siempre la importancia a lo que estaba pasando con su entrevistado y no estaba buscando figurar o ganar más likes en alguna parte.
eso se ha perdido en nuestra tv, y hemos ganado chabacanería, muchas faltas de respeto de todo tipo, y por eso y muchos otros temas a tratar otro día es que la tv abierta esta cada día peor. 
#respeto, #televisionchilena, #entrevistas, #metoo, #respect, #viña2019.

text:
durch ihre 2017 im magazin „the new yorker“ veröffentlichte kurzgeschichte „cat person“ löste kristen roupenian einen regelrechten viralen hype aus. tausendfach wurde diese geschichte geteilt und damit zur meistdiskutiertesten story der #metoo-debatte.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
der bei blumenbar erschienene sammelband „cat person“ enthält oben genannte story und 11 weitere kurzgeschichten aus ihrer feder. nicht alle stories sind perfekt, aber dennoch beweist kristen roupenian einen scharfen blick für zwischenmenschliche beziehungen, abhängigkeiten, unangenehme wahrheiten und heizt die diskussion um das kräfte- und machtverhältnis zwischen frauen und männern weiter an.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
die geschichten erzählen das alltäglich unsagbare, beschreiben besondere gefühle, kommen ein wenig seltsam daher, sogar mit einem hauch verbotenem und greifen die unterschiedlichsten themen auf. so geht es zum beispiel um einen herzensbrecher, der eigentlich nur nett sein will, ein paar, das seinen übernachtungsgast beim sex lauschen lässt, ein tinder-date mit masochistischen vorlieben, ein kleines mädchen, das sich böses wünscht oder eine frau, die beharrlich vom gedanken verfolgt wird, ihren neuen nervigen kollegen zu beißen. lauter kurzgeschichten, die es in sich haben und die man nicht so schnell vergisst!
⠀⠀⠀⠀
kristen roupenian nimmt kein blatt vor den mund. prägnant und unverhohlen schreibt sie über unsere heutige gesellschaft mit all ihren facetten, schwächen und unzulänglichkeiten. denn alle menschen sind irgendwie auch böse, gemein, hinterlistig, eigennützig, egoistisch und ein klein wenig verrückt. eine sehr zeitgemäße kurzgeschichtensammlung - laut, kompromisslos und vor allem sehr #metoo.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
zu meinen persönlichen highlights gehören „cat person“, „ein netter typ“ und „die beißerin“.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#wassilkeliest #kristenroupenian #catperson #blumenbarverlag #booksofblumenbar #aufbauverlag @aufbau_verlag #shortstories #kurzgeschichten #ilovebooks #leseempfehlung #buchtipp #bücherliebe #bücherwurm #lesezeit #leseratte #bookstagram #instabook #buchnerd #bookaholic #lesenmachtsüchtig #lesenistliebe #lesefreude #neverstopreading #daslesenistschön #ausliebezudenbüchern #lesenmachtglücklich #makereadinggreatagain

text:
i lost my virginity to assault. i was raised by a parent who struggled with addiction which lead to a lot of neglect/abuse. i coped with alcohol in my teens. i struggled with mental health and turned to self harm. i got into a lot of really, really bad situations. i was looking for love and attention in any place possible.
.
.
eventually, no one was left to hear my sob story. the darkest days call for drastic measures. i had to learn that everything i needed, i already had. i worked on my mental health and found proper ways to cope. in time, i turned my own tragedy into triumph. it was and will always be an uphill battle for me. so, if you are going through something, let yourself go through it. hold on! prove how strong you really are. climb that mountain. and when you get to the top, come out with your arms held high! ❤️

text:
i've spoken about reinforcement learning before. rl is when an agent takes an action, gets feedback from the environment and learns from it 🎮⁣
⁣
a "policy" is something an agent follows to pick an action from a state. ⁣
⁣
q-learning is a method that learns from experience and gives an optimal policy i.e. a policy that will choose actions so as to maximize reward ➕⁣
⁣
q-learning is a model-free method, which means it doesn't even need a model of the environment to learn the policy. ⁣
⁣
basically, q-learning is woke af🤩⁣
⁣
</>⁣
⁣

text:
gras créature. ______________
hier, j'ai découvert que la fille de kirov était morte tragiquement. elle est morte de faim et de soif dans l'obscurité. il n'y avait pas de mère à côté d'elle. sa mère l'a laissée seule à la maison.
le premier" laissez-les parler " est sorti de la transmission. c'est thrash. mais c'est le thrash du temps moderne.
la société a explosé, émouvant et criant: sur le nombre de lui. les hommes criaient le plus . sur le pieu, alors mettre sur le pieu la mère de cette fille.la grosse chose, le nouveau nom de la mère de la fille décédée, qui lui a donné la société.
mais personne n'a demandé pourquoi "la grosse chose" a permis à un si petit enfant. personne ne s'est souvenu, et sur quels finances il y avait cette «grosse créature»? qu'est-ce qu'ils mangeaient? qu'est-ce qu'il y avait à payer pour l'appartement? pour quoi acheter des vêtements?
vous dites qu'elle avait des amis? amis, voisins????? ce sont ceux qui ont été demandés, et savaient-ils l'existence d'un petit enfant dans la « créature grasse» ? bien sûr ne le savaient pas. vous ne saviez pas ou ne vouliez pas savoir?
est-ce que j'avais besoin d'une «grosse chose» de ma propre mère? est-ce que la» grosse créature " avait une mère?
et avant de mettre sur le pieu « grosse créature» pour comprendre, ce n'est pas pour longtemps.d'une interview avec ses camarades de classe, nous comprenons que la petite "grosse créature" a été donnée à elle-même. depuis l'enfance, j'ai toujours traîné dans la cour.très probablement, la "créature grasse" a été inculquée depuis l'enfance par l'idée qu'elle est apparue par erreur. qu'elle est superflue. diplômée de l'école . l'éducation?la profession? non. les filles, en règle générale, qui sentent inconsciemment qu'elles n'ont pas besoin de leurs mères, se marient tôt ou cohabitent avec le sexe opposé.à 17 ans, "la grosse créature" est tombée enceinte du concubin, et apparemment plus tôt, elle est tombée avec lui. créer une famille. et ici n'est pas de la chance. le gars a abandonné la "grosse chose" quand leur fille nouveau-né avait 8 mois. ________ suite dans les commentaires

text:
the me too movement is a powerful one. women all over the globe are finding their voices and using them! i love this time in our history. women like ruth bader ginsburg and christine blasey ford make me proud to be a woman. i can absolutely claim the #metoo with some stories that will make cry in your coffee cup, but that’s not what i’m writing about. you see what’s on my heart is our men. have some men participated in shameful acts and the degradation of women? absolutely. and these men deserve to be held accountable. but how are we, as women, different? how do we come into power and wield it differently than the men have? men have owned their power (as a whole) selfishly, withholding it from certain genders, classes, and races. how do we as women say “me too” and “no more” and “never again” without shaming all men and creating an imbalanced matriarchy? how do we set an example of what it’s like to be graceful stewards of power?
how do we say “no more” while also saying “we still love and want you to be your strong, brave, manly self?”
you see, it’s a common reaction to be punishing with power once it’s claimed after a time period of not having it. let’s be careful not to punish our men. after all, we’re better than that. as women, let’s be graceful stewards of power.
⠀⠀
#metoo #brave #women #wearelove #powerful #bestrong #metoomovement #girlpower #feminism #womensupportingwomen #empowerwomen #supportwomen #nomore #findyourvoice #accountable #intuitiveliving

so i started march's book early and am already a fair way in! womanhood @barereality is a collection of 100 photographs and interviews with women and their vulvas - all about being a woman and it's one of the most powerful books i've ever read. please read it!

the shame and embarrassment myself and so many other women end up feeling over this amazing and fascinating part of our bodies is crazy! it's designed to give us intense pleasure, to birth children and to pleasure others! have you ever looked at yours?! the stories in this book made me feel normal, and like part of a group of amazing women that can be proud of their vaginas, no matter what they look like, how much hair is on them or the history they've been through! thank you to every one of them that shared their stories, i hope a lot of people read and learn from them! 
#womanhood #feminist #timetotalk #metoo #learning #vaginas #women #proud

todas somos seres de luz y conservamos magia por dentro. 💫
magia especial, capaz de hacernos brillar y destacar del resto. esta solo está esperándote para que la reconozcas, la tomes y puedas sentir toda su energía y vibra. depende de ti tomar la elección de tu vida y es que el camino correcto, puede ser difícil en ocasiones por diversos pensamientos en nuestra mente o por críticas de personas “comunes” que dejamos que se queden dentro de nuestro ser.🌪🌤
sin importar que suceda en tu camino reconoce las oportunidades que nos da la vida para que encuentres esa magia en ti porque el camino comienza cuando eres consciente de que todas las cosas en nuestra vida no ocurren por naturaleza y que tú eres la causante de la supuesta magia. 🙋🏻‍♀️👸🏻

text:
i can remember those days when i’d walk the halls with my head hung low. when i would fidget with things in my locker, desperately waiting for people to pass. when i would skip lunch, hide in the bathroom, or spend class in the nurse’s office. when i felt destined to fail, like i had no purpose. or when the experience of “all eyes on me” was an excruciating one.

this time, i could finally walk up and down those halls with confidence, use my voice, not care about approval, but instead, just be me. more importantly, a version of me that finally possessed a sense of self worth, and a sense of purpose - an important mission to lead change.

as a speaker, i feel blessed to speak at any school. however, visiting my old high school, the school where my greatest struggles started, was a gift. things coming full circle... is a thing. and today, i’m spending a little time feeling pretty grateful just thinking about it.
.
.
.
#leadthechange #surpassyourpast #rise #bewhoyouvealwaysbeenmeanttobe

text:
today we released a new post on our blog, the nightingale! we are happy to share allison linne’s piece, this is a normal bus ride. in this memoir, linne speaks to the disheartening normalization of sexual violence which can lead to survivors feeling invisible and isolated. while the world continues on, linne silently suffers on the morning bus route; however, the hope in this piece comes from allison linne's courage to break the silence surrounding the aftermath of assault in the hopes of making other survivors feel seen and validated in their pain.

text:
🖤 r e q u i e m to r e d e e m 🖤 #thursdaythoughts 
there is no right nor wrong, good nor bad; there is only what works & what does not work, especially when referring to the complexities of human behavior. it’s incredibly easy to demonize those who have made catastrophically selfish decisions that affect others so deeply. from the #mindcontrol & severe abuse that i endured while a child in the religious sex cult, to the violence from my dad & domestic partners throughout my life, to almost losing my life at knife point by an ex on my 25th birthday, to my dads suicide in 2016 - & much more; i have many reasonable excuses to hold onto this character of “victim”. i likely will find that i am challenged with mind-body, psychosomatic issues for the rest of this vessels journey due to this & yet none of this is about blaming or shaming those who have harmed me & my family. 
today, i’m posting not only about the concept of this idea that we can practice forgiving those who have actively hurt us, but also about how we can come from genuine compassion for those whom seek #redemption 🖤 
it seems it’s much easier to forgive those who seek forgiveness, in my experience. and perhaps it is. however for this instance, i’m specifically referring to the historic #cohentestimony #cohenhearing that we witnessed yesterday. my heart and soul goes out to #michaelcohen for the courage it took to come forward and admit his demons & take responsibility at the risk of losing his career, family, reputation, and now his freedom... i admire his professional brevity while being attacked & threatened by humans who only know how to lash out when experiencing emotionally unintelligent fearfulness. i’m encouraged by his #awakening for numerous reasons; one being that it displays hope that even the corrupt, greedy, & ridiculously selfish humans can find redemption for their soul’s journey. with all that i’ve experienced in my life from the extreme abuse & neglect to the chronic illnesses that surfaced during it all, & then facing losing my dad to suicide in the same week that the #uselection was rigged in the favor of a human that comes from extreme #narcissism & bullying (continued🔽)
name: i am human | so are you
